---
description: Restart InkFlow dev server after code changes
alwaysApply: true
---

After completing any implementation, fix, or meaningful code change in this project:

1. Stop any process on ports 3000/3001 if needed.
2. Run `npm run db:push` when `prisma/schema.prisma` or migrations changed.
3. Start `npm run dev` in the background from the project root.
4. Confirm the server is ready at http://localhost:3000 (or report the alternate port).

This Next.js app serves both frontend pages and `/api/*` backend routes in one dev process — restarting `npm run dev` refreshes both.

Briefly tell the user the server was refreshed and the URL to open.
